        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 12:59PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1259 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mulberry, or 10 miles east of Valley Grande, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deatsville, Autaugaville, Billingsley, Booth, Mulberry, Marbury, Vida
Junction, Dawson Mill, and New Prospect.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
